<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When a big crypto company goes bankrupt for mi=
susing customer money, there are at least two possible vectors for contagio=
n:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Other big crypto companies that were =
customers of or lenders to that big crypto company might have lost money, p=
ossibly rendering them insolvent, and there will be rumors and worries abou=
t what companies were exposed and how bad things could be.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Other big crypto companies will get questions like=
, =E2=80=9Cwell, wait, if=C2=A0<em>those guys=C2=A0</em>were a big scam, do=
es that mean that=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>are also a big scam?=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Grayscale Bitcoin Trust is a publicly trad=
ed investment company registered with the US Securities and Exchange Commis=
sion that just holds a bunch of Bitcoin.=C2=A0It files <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29765114.257546/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTU4ODQ4OS8wMDAxMTkzMTI1MjIwNTM1M=
DEvZDI4OTI1MWQxMGsuaHRtI2ZpbjI4OTI1MV8y/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8b7e93d8" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;"> audited financial statements</a>=C2=A0saying how many Bitcoins it =
has. Do you believe those statements? Should you? Here I want to emphasize =
that nothing in this column is ever investing advice, particularly about cr=
ypto, dear lord, but still I must confess my bias that I think that most au=
dited financial statements of most US public companies are mostly true. Obv=
iously one can get up to a lot of nonsense with accounting, but Grayscale=
=E2=80=99s accounts are extremely simple, and presumably the audit consists=
 mostly of checking to see if the Bitcoins are there. Is it possible for au=
ditors to get that one wrong? I mean, the probability is not=C2=A0<em>zero<=
/em>. Me, though, I like an audit.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Grayscale is now trading at about a 45% discou=
nt to its net asset value, meaning that $100 of Bitcoin in Grayscale=E2=80=
=99s pot of Bitcoin is worth just $55 on the stock market. Part of the reas=
on for this is market concern about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/29765114.257546/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xM=
S8xNy9idXNpbmVzcy9mdHgtY3J5cHRvLWNvbnRhZ2lvbi1zYmYuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB25216945" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> contagion to Grayscale=E2=80=99s parent company<=
/a>, Digital Currency Group, whose Genesis trading unit paused redemptions =
last week due to FTX fallout. But part of it seems to be about not trusting=
 anyone. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29765114.=
257546/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMS8yMS9ncmF5c2NhbGUtd29udC1zaGFy=
